The paper discusses differentially-private algorithms for approximating the 2nd-moment matrix of data, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) since the paper deals with privacy-preserving algorithms. The paper also involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in the form of Bayesian inference.
